article.headline: Cent. Connecticut St. 76, Binghamton 51
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- Ken Horton scored 20 and added 10 rebounds to lead Central Connecticut to an easy 76-51 win over Binghamton on Tuesday. Joe Seymore added 14 for Central Connecticut (1-3), while Aaron Hall had 13. Binghamton was abysmal from 3-point range, finishing 0-for-19, three short of the NCAA record for the most 3-pointers tried without a make (Canisius, 1995). D.J. Rivera had 13 points and Reggie Fuller added 12 and 10 rebounds to lead Binghamton (1-3). Central Connecticut led 28-24 at the break, but pulled away with 25-11 run. Binghamton got as close as 12, but Hall answered with three straight three-point plays to put the game away.
